pr_body:
**Description:**

- This PR updates NPM Scripts
- Also, updates workflows to accommodate the change in scripts

**Description:**

- Updates some `for` loops which uses `.push()` to use `Array.from()`
- Why? 
    - Array.from() is much faster compared to .push() when used with for loops

More Info: https://measurethat.net/Benchmarks/Show/25686/0/push-vs-create-fill-and-map-vs-create-with-arrayfrom

**Description:**

In some cases, `Array.from()` is faster by almost 2x when compared to `.push()` 

More Info: https://measurethat.net/Benchmarks/Show/25686/0/push-vs-create-fill-and-map-vs-create-with-arrayfrom

**Description:**

- Used Array.from() instead of .push()

pr_title: [Chore] - Updated CI and Added Caching Feature
pr_body:
**Description:**

- Updated CodeQL Workflow
- Enabled Caching for Workflows
- We won't be caching `node_modules` as according to https://github.com/actions/cache/blob/main/examples.md#node---npm, it is not recommended

Instead of using `npm install` we would be using `npm ci` which is usually used for CI Environments

[{'comment_id': 1237388461, 'comment_body': 'Why?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 21, 18, 3, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'dkoes', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1237392117, 'comment_body': 'I found a pretty good blog related to improving jest test speeds, https://dev.to/vantanev/make-your-jest-tests-up-to-20-faster-by-changing-a-single-setting-i36 and according to it `--runInBand` is useful in resource-constrained environments like CI, where the overhead of worker processes is higher than the speedup of running tests in parallel.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 21, 18, 6, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'adithyaakrishna', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1237396827, 'comment_body': 'I also benched the tests using https://github.com/sharkdp/hyperfine and these are the results that I got. pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 1257528921, 'comment_body': 'Removed the Build job, which saves us ~56 seconds in terms of combined CI time wrt CodeQL and Build Workflows But why this change? Our `package.json` has a `"postInstall"` script here, https://github.com/3dmol/3Dmol.js/blob/master/package.json#L33 which runs `npm run build` upon installation of dependencies. Till now we were running a redundant job, hence removed the same `postInstall` running after installation of dependencies With Build Job = +28 seconds - Which was Duplicated by the above `postInstall` script ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 7, 9, 19, 11, 15, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'adithyaakrishna', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1259736959, 'comment_body': "This is here for a reason - so VS code doesn't report errors where there are none.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 7, 11, 13, 26, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'dkoes', 'type': 'User'}]
